HEADWORD: Castigatory
<hw>Cas`ti*ga*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>castigatorius</ets>.]</ety> <def>Punitive in order to amendment;
corrective.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Castigatory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Castigatory
<hw>Cas"ti*ga*to*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An instrument formerly used
to punish and correct arrant scolds; -- called also a <altname>ducking
stool</altname>, or <altname>trebucket</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Blacktone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Castile soap</ent>⟦br⟧
